OL,4,C'catastrophic' warns principal
OL,6,FShe said: "I'm just disappointed that
OL,7,Fagain there are always things that are
OL,8,Fbeing implemented they're not allowed
OL,9,Fto be embedded for us to understand
OL,10,Fwhere it could work better or where
OL,11,Fthings are completely wrong and then
OL,12,Fnew things are put in place again
OL,13,Fwithout consultation of the people
OL,14,Fit's actually going to affect."
OL,16,FThe Met faced a #260 million gap in
OL,17,Ffunding gap which meant the force had
OL,18,Fto reallocate money to different
OL,19,Fdepartments.
